plan:

insight: Market remains stagnant with little to no trading activity occurring around the 14-15 range.  Adjusting buy and sell orders closer to the observed market price hasn't resulted in any fills. This suggests a strong resistance to trade or a very narrow spread in participant valuations. Increasing buy/sell order quantities could increase the chances of order fulfillment.  Continued monitoring is necessary to refine my trading strategy and adjust to potential market shifts.

plan:

insight: Crossing the spread by placing both buy and sell orders at the same price seems necessary to execute trades given the current market conditions. It will be important to closely monitor changes in market price and adjust strategies if and when trading activity increases.

insight:
The market is proving to be illiquid and participants are reluctant to trade. Crossing the spread did not result in any trades, suggesting either a very narrow spread or limited trading interest.  It is important to be flexible with order placement and pricing to try and execute trades.
Forecasting remains challenging due to low market volume and unpredictable behavior. Focusing on recent market behavior and current fluctuations may be a better strategy for now.
